## setup etrade Subcommand
File: subcmds/setup/etrade.go
Flags: --consumer-key, --consumer-secret, --data-dir, --sandbox

OAuth helpers in etrade/setup.go (standalone, no Client needed):
  - oauthSignSetup() — package-level signing; reuses oauthEscape from client.go
  - OAuthRequestToken() — GET /oauth/request_token, oauth_callback=oob
  - OAuthAccessToken() — GET /oauth/access_token with verifier
  - OAuthListAccounts() — GET /v1/accounts/list, returns []Account

Interactive flow in subcmds/setup/etrade.go:
  1. OAuthRequestToken → short-lived request token
  2. Print https://us.etrade.com/e/t/etws/authorize?key=KEY&token=TOKEN
  3. Read verifier from stdin
  4. OAuthAccessToken → long-lived access token
  5. OAuthListAccounts → print accounts
  6. If >1 account: prompt for accountIdKey; if 1: auto-select
  7. Write secrets.json (merges with existing file)

## server/server.go Changes
  - loadSecrets() check includes ETrade (coinbase || coinex || etrade)
  - Start() block creates etrade.NewExchange(ctx, s.db, secrets.ETrade, opts)
  - initServerState includes "etrade": {EnabledProductIDs: []string{}}
  - New() patches loaded state with any exchanges in initServerState missing
    from the persisted DB state — handles existing DBs predating etrade support
